
#False idol, sometimes refering to the worship of money.  From the biblical story of the golden calf.
#A golden calf statue that was worshiped as a god by the Israelites while Moses was atop Mount Horeb recieving the ten commandments (Ex. 32).  The idolatry caused God's "wrath" to "wax hot against them."  Moses begged god to "turn thy fierce wrath...[from] thy people."  When he decended the Mount, he "burnt [the golded calf] in the fire, and ground it to powder, and strawed it upon the water."